-- Opel meeting in Berlin delayed due to Magna-GM talks
-- 
-- Fri May 29, 2009 10:36am EDT
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2009/05/29/us-gm-opel-delay-sb-idUSTRE54S3HX20090529

 

 BERLIN  (Reuters) - A top-level meeting in Berlin on the future of the Opel unit of General Motors has been delayed until 12 p.m. EDT due to ongoing talks between GM and Magna, a German government spokesman said on Friday. 

 The meeting had been scheduled to start at 10 a.m. EDT. (Reporting by  Gernot Heller )